### **job description:**


there are multiple **ml research scientist / ml engineer – surgical applications** positions available at edda technology, princeton, nj. responsibilities include:

* use state\-of\-the\-art ai technologies to research, develop and deploy real\-time, low\-latency surgical ai solutions; •
* develop and integrate ai agent and/or deep reinforcement learning (drl) based frameworks for intelligent decision\-making, workflow automation, or adaptive optimization in intraoperative video;
* actively stay current with the latest developments in ai research and emerging technologies;
* understand clinical needs to solve real\-world problems and drive the design, development, and validation of new methods of ai clinical solutions.
* conforming to the company’s standard/procedure of product development;
* efficiently communicate with project managers and team members on the execution;
* other job responsibilities as assigned by the management.

**candidates shall meet part of the below qualifications**:

* experience with advanced vlm/sfm/llm models (e.g., gpt\-4o, unisurg/surgmotion, sam) for intraoperative video analysis;
* experience and skills in working with deep reinforcement learning (deep rl) and/or ai agent frameworks, including prompt engineering, langchain/llamaindex or rag;
* experience with nvidia stacks and hardware deployment is a plus;
* strong foundational knowledge in geometric computer vision (camera calibration, slam, registration, multi\-view geometry) and deep learning (classification, tracking, mapping, transformers/cnns);
* 3\+ years of experience in ai, ml, dl or related fields;
* excellent software engineering skills in using c/c\+\+; other software skills preferred include python, pytorch, tensor flow, and keras;
* strong problem\-solving skills with the ability to rapidly implement, verify, and iterate on solutions;
* collaborative team player who is highly self\-motivated, with a proven ability to learn quickly and thrive in dynamic, high\-impact environments.
* clear communication skills in english;
* phd in ai/ml/cs or related field or master’s degree with minimum 3 years of industry experience.

**desired qualifications:**

* strong algorithm development skills with in\-depth knowledge on medical image analysis/segmentation and image registration;
* experience with tensorrt and/or 3d visualization programming in linux;
* knowledge in human anatomy and interpretation of medical images;
* hands\-on experience and knowledge in dicom a plus;
* experience working with medical imaging modalities (endoscopic video, ultrasound, ct) or similar sensor data

### **company introduction:**


excellent opportunity with a dynamic, growing medical technology solution company.


edda technology is an innovative leader in the rapidly growing field of intelligent robotic solutions for precision surgery. pioneering a “fully quantitative, interactive” approach to intelligent imaging analytics and robotic integration, the company has built a proprietary technology platform to facilitate pre\-surgical planning and simulation, intra\-operative navigation, post\-operative evaluation. with its end\-to\-end enabling platform, edda’s goal is to form a comprehensive ecosystem of clinical practice, connection, and education to support physicians and patient management in all tiers of hospitals. iqqa® is a registered trademark of edda technology. (www.eddatech.com)

### **compensation/ benefits**


salary range: $135,000 \- $200,000; compensation is based on experience, education, and relevant skills.


edda offers a competitive salary, performance\-based incentive stock options, and excellent benefits including medical and dental insurance, vision care, 401k plan, section 125 health and dependent care (flexible spending) accounts, and paid vacations. the company sponsors the h1\-b application.

**send applications to:** hiring@edda\-tech.com

langan provides expert land development engineering and environmental consulting services for major developers, renewable energy producers, energy companies, corporations, healthcare systems, colleges/universities, and large infrastructure programs throughout the u.s. and around the world. our employees collaborate seamlessly among 50\+ offices and gain valuable hands\-on experience that fosters career growth. langan culture is entrepreneurial from advancing innovative technical solutions, to participating in robust training and knowledge sharing, to making progressive change within the communities we live and work.





consistently ranked among the top ten “best firms to work for” and engineering news\-record’s top 50 firms worldwide, langan attracts and retains the best talent in the industry. employees thrive at langan, a firm that fosters an inclusive and supportive work environment for all; prioritizes wellbeing, health, and safety; encourages volunteerism and philanthropy; offers workplace flexibility, along with carbon\-neutral office spaces; and empowers individuals to contribute their skills and knowledge to make impactful contributions.

**job summary**
---------------


langan is seeking an **ai engineer** to join its collaborative team in **dallas, tx**. this individual will serve a key function in experimenting with emerging techniques, rapidly prototyping solutions, validating value through pilots, and scaling successful concepts into reliable, production\-ready systems. in this role, you will have the opportunity to design, build, and deploy full\-stack ai applications that solve real engineering and business challenges.

**job responsibilities**
------------------------


* design, build, and maintain production\-grade backend services, rest apis, and data pipelines in python and/or node.js that power ai\-driven applications at scale;
* build and ship responsive, user\-centered front\-end applications using react and modern javascript, with a focus on performance, accessibility, and intuitive design;
* architect and optimize llm\-powered features on azure openai, including prompt engineering, rag pipelines, tool/function calling, and fine\-tuning, to deliver reliable, production\-quality ai capabilities;
* lead rapid prototyping efforts (spikes, proofs\-of\-concept, and mvps) to de\-risk ideas, demonstrate feasibility, and accelerate adoption of high\-impact ai capabilities;
* bridge the gap between ai model capabilities and real\-world user needs, translating ambiguous requirements into well\-scoped, high\-impact product features;
* partner with engineers, project managers, and discipline leads across langan to surface high\-value ai integration opportunities and scope technically sound solutions;
* proactively identify and prototype automation opportunities that reduce manual burden on engineering teams and accelerate project delivery;
* communicate clearly with non\-technical stakeholders, translating system performance, model behavior, and technical tradeoffs into actionable insights for leadership;
* work on multiple project timelines simultaneously; and
* perform other duties as requested.
**qualifications**
------------------


* bachelor’s degree in computer science or related field. advanced degree is preferred;
* internship experience in software engineering or applied ai roles;
* hands\-on proficiency with python and/or javascript (node.js), react, and the azure ecosystem (azure openai, azure functions, app services). familiarity with ml libraries such as langchain or similar frameworks is a plus;
* experience with ai\-assisted development tools (e.g., claude code, openai codex, github copilot) to accelerate implementation, improve code quality, and support documentation;
* excellent written and verbal communication skills;
* strong attention to detail with excellent analytical, multitasking, and judgment capabilities; and
* ability to effectively work independently and in a team environment;

